quran[25]{c,v,t}:
  21,51,"Indeed We had, before this, granted Abraham discretion and his particular consciousness of truth, and We knew him very well (in all aspects of his character)"
  21,52,"He said to his father and people: \"What are these images to which you pay such sincere devotion"
  21,53,"They said: \"We have found our forefathers worshipping them"
  21,54,"So, it is certain that,\" said he, \"both of you, you and your forefathers, have been in obvious error"
  21,55,"They asked: \"Is it the truth that you are proclaiming to us or are you jesting"
  21,56,"He answered: \"No, but your Lord is the Lord of the heavens and the earth, Who has originated them, each with particular features, and I am one to bear witness to this truth"
  21,57,"And (he made a decision:) \"By God, I will most certainly devise a plan against your idols as soon as you have turned your backs and gone away"
  21,58,"And then he broke all of them to pieces except the one biggest in their sight, so that they might be able turn back to it (to ask what had happened)"
  21,59,"Who has done all this to our deities?\" they exclaimed. \"Indeed, he is one of the worst wrongdoers"
  21,60,"Some said: \"We heard a young man make mention of them, who is called Abraham"
  21,61,"They said: \"Then bring him before the people’s eyes, so that they may bear witness against him"
  21,62,"Abraham,\" they asked, \"is it you who has done this to our deities"
  21,63,"He answered: \"Rather, (some doer) must have done it – this is the biggest of them. Ask them, if they are able to speak"
  21,64,"So they turned to their conscious nature which awoke to truth, and said (among themselves): \"You (we), it is you (we) who are the wrongdoers"
  21,65,"But afterwards, (under the influence of the same factors causing them to disbelieve) they relapsed into their former way of believing, and said to Abraham: \"You know very well that these (images) cannot speak"
  21,66,"(Abraham) said: \"Then, do you worship, instead of God, that which cannot benefit you in any way, nor harm you"
  21,67,Shame on you and on all that you worship instead of God! Will you not reason and understand
  21,68,"They exclaimed: \"Burn him and so protect your deities, if you really mean to do something"
  21,69,"O fire,\" We ordered, \"Be cool and peaceful for Abraham"
  21,70,"They had schemed to destroy him but We frustrated them, making them the worst of losers"
  21,71,"We saved him and Lot (who believed in him), guiding them to the land (of Damascus, including Palestine) in which We have produced many blessings for all peoples"
  21,72,"We bestowed upon him Isaac, and as an additional gift, Jacob (for grandson); and each We made righteous"
  21,73,"And We made them leaders guiding people by Our command, and We revealed to them to do good deeds, and to establish the Prayer in conformity with its conditions, and pay the Prescribed Purifying Alms. They were Our servants devoted to worshipping us with all sincerity"
  21,74,"And Lot too (We made a leader), to whom We granted sound, wise judgment, and revealed knowledge, and We saved him from the people of the land who were given to deeds of corruption. Truly, they were a wicked people lost in transgression"
  21,75,We embraced him in Our mercy; surely he was among the righteous